The Agudama Ekpetiama Division of the Bayelsa Police Command has been attacked by unidentified gunmen.
In the attack that took place last night, the DPO, a sergeant, and an unspecified number of men were killed while arms and ammunition were carted away, according to the stateâ€™s command.
Two others were also injured, and are being treated at the Niger Delta University Teaching Hospital, Okolobiri.
The command has warned all stations to be on the alert.

			
